<paragraph id="8BF336AEFF94AC34748E3A55FB6C11A3" blockId="2.[136,1452,1626,2084]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Distribution of the 
<typeStatus id="54F7880CFF94AC3475603A55FE7B116B" box="[358,406,1626,1652]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">type</typeStatus>
subspecies extends from northern 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC34772E3A55FC69116B" box="[808,900,1626,1652]" name="Albania" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Albania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3477943A55FBF3116B" box="[914,1054,1626,1652]" name="Serbia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Montenegro</collectingCountry>
, North 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3470713A55FB1B116B" box="[1143,1270,1626,1652]" name="Macedonia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Macedonia</collectingCountry>
, eastern 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC34715B3A55FA4A116B" box="[1373,1447,1626,1652]" name="Serbia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Serbia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC34748E3A71FF0F1187" box="[136,226,1662,1688]" name="Kosovo" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Kosovo</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3474E83A71FEA31187" box="[238,334,1662,1688]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
and north-east 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3475FB3A71FDA11187" box="[509,588,1662,1688]" name="Greece" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Greece</collectingCountry>
(with exception of parts of Mt. 
<collectingRegion id="4988F84CFF94AC3477B23A71FC161186" box="[948,1019,1662,1689]" country="Greece" name="Agion Oros" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Athos</collectingRegion>
), through the European part of 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC34715D3A71FA461187" box="[1371,1451,1662,1688]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and north-east 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC34752B3AADFE6011A3" box="[301,397,1698,1724]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Anatolia</collectingCountry>
up to the Caucasus in the 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3476B23AADFC6111A3" box="[692,908,1698,1724]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Russian Federation</collectingCountry>
and western 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3470263AADFB9011A3" box="[1056,1149,1698,1724]" name="Georgia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Georgia</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF336AEFF94AC3574BB3AC9FEE4163B" blockId="2.[136,1452,1626,2084]" lastBlockId="3.[136,1451,158,292]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="64" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
The synonymised name 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D2DFF94AC3475CA3AC9FD1411FF" authority="C. Koch" authorityName="C. Koch" box="[460,761,1734,1760]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Senecio" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rariflorus">
<emphasis id="B938EABCFF94AC3475CA3AC9FD7B11FF" box="[460,662,1734,1760]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Senecio rariflorus</emphasis>
C. Koch
</taxonomicName>
was established on the basis of material from “Ossia” – 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC34716C3AC9FF30101B" name="South Ossetia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">South Ossetia</collectingCountry>
, Caucasus. “ 
<emphasis id="B938EABCFF94AC34756C3AE5FB8A1037" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Maxime accredit ad 
<taxonomicName id="4C4C4D2DFF94AC34764D3AE5FD20101B" authorityName="C. A. Meyer" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="M. Bieb." box="[587,717,1770,1796]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jacobaea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="othonnae">S. othonnae</taxonomicName>
M.B., sed huic specie sunt Pinnae sessiles, Calathidia sub 8-flora; Anthodium sub-8-phyllum et ligulae latae, apice dentate. In Ossia [Ossetia] frequenter
</emphasis>
”. In the detailed description also its glabrosity “ 
<emphasis id="B938EABCFF94AC3475593B3DFE051053" box="[351,488,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">glaberrimus</emphasis>
” is mentioned. In an account of his journeys, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDD4B5FFF94AC3477E33B3DFB9F1053" author="Koch, K." box="[997,1138,1842,1868]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refId="ref4459" refString="Koch, K. (1843) Reise durch Russland nach dem kaukasischen Isthmus in den Jahren 1836, 1837 und 1838, vol. 2. J. G. Cotta, Stuttgart &amp; Tubingen, 559 pp." type="book" year="1843">Koch (1843)</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that he collected this species from two sites: one (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDD4B5FFF94AC3475FD3B59FD4B106E" author="Koch, K." box="[507,678,1878,1905]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refId="ref4459" refString="Koch, K. (1843) Reise durch Russland nach dem kaukasischen Isthmus in den Jahren 1836, 1837 und 1838, vol. 2. J. G. Cotta, Stuttgart &amp; Tubingen, 559 pp." type="book" year="1843">Koch 1843: 64</bibRefCitation>
) from Ossetia, locality Tapan (Tagiani) not far from Dschawi (Dzau in Ossetian, Dzhava or today Java in Georgian), and the other (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDD4B5FFF94AC34774D3B75FBEE108A" author="Koch, K." box="[843,1027,1914,1941]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" refId="ref4459" refString="Koch, K. (1843) Reise durch Russland nach dem kaukasischen Isthmus in den Jahren 1836, 1837 und 1838, vol. 2. J. G. Cotta, Stuttgart &amp; Tubingen, 559 pp." type="book" year="1843">Koch 1843: 136</bibRefCitation>
) from the locality Glola (today out of the western border of 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3475833B91FDCB10A6" box="[389,550,1950,1977]" name="South Ossetia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">South Ossetia</collectingCountry>
); see also 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDD4B5FFF94AC34769B3B91FCC110A7" author="Lack, H. W." box="[669,812,1950,1976]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="79 - 94" refId="ref4499" refString="Lack, H. W. (1978) The Turkish and Caucasian collections of C. Koch, II. Caucasia. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 37: 79 - 94." type="journal article" year="1978">Lack (1978)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFDD4B5FFF94AC34773E3B91FBDF10A6" author="Ledebour, C. F. von" box="[824,1074,1949,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="463 - 718" refId="ref4572" refString="Ledebour, C. F. von (1845) Flora Rossica, vol. 2 (2,6). E. Schweizerbart, Stuttgart, pp. 463 - 718. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 6606" type="book chapter" year="1845">Ledebour (1845: 637)</bibRefCitation>
indicates the presence of Koch’s specimens in Berlin “ 
<emphasis id="B938EABCFF94AC3475873BCDFDB710C3" box="[385,602,1986,2012]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">in herb. reg. berol.</emphasis>
”, but there are no specimens by Koch preserved in Berlin today. Most of his specimens kept in Berlin were destroyed during the World War II (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDD4B5FFF94AC3477BB3BE9FAC51F1F" author="Edmondson, J. R. &amp; Lack, H. W." box="[957,1320,2022,2048]" pageId="2" pageNumber="63" pagination="321 - 344" refId="ref4251" refString="Edmondson, J. R. &amp; Lack, H. W. (1977) Turkish and Caucasian collections of C. Koch I. Turkey. Notes from the Royal Botanic Garden Edinburgh 35: 321 - 344." type="journal article" year="1977">Edmondson &amp; Lack 1977: 321</bibRefCitation>
). There are two Koch’s specimens preserved in Paris. One with the label “ 
<emphasis id="B938EABCFF94AC3477413405FBDF1F3B" box="[839,1074,2058,2084]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">
Russisch – 
<collectingCountry id="F35B763EFF94AC3477C33405FBDF1F3B" box="[965,1074,2058,2084]" name="Armenia" pageId="2" pageNumber="63">Armenien</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
” (P03729657, http://mediaphoto. mnhn.fr/media/1441347947308ClHfLzHVvGpNeQGp), with Koch’s original handwriting and the other (P03729654, https://mediaphoto.mnhn.fr/media/16130588644386xngNRm4KlRdTHFe) labelled as “Tschaweusgebiet” with a nonoriginal, transcribed label. The latter specimen was selected as a 
<typeStatus id="54F7880CFF95AC3577683CE9FC38161F" box="[878,981,230,256]" pageId="3" pageNumber="64">lectotype</typeStatus>
because of the good conformity with the protologue.
</paragraph>
